What you need to know:  Everton's huge win at a raucous Goodison Park means Frank Lampard's side are just two points from safety and have a game in hand to come over Leeds and BurnleyArsenal were 2-1 winners at West Ham to move back above Spurs, who earlier beat Leicester 3-1 thanks to a Son Heung-min doubleMikel Arteta's men will hope to extend their lead to five points next weekend when they host relegation-threatened Leeds, while Spurs face a daunting trip to title-chasing Liverpool